# Intuition
In this question we have to find the **Maximum Profit**.
So, we find the **stock with Minimum value** and then **check for maximum profit**.
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach
    Example : prices = [7,1,5,3,6,4]
    Initially `minValue` = INT_MAX, `profit` = 0
    At index `0` 
        `minValue` = min(minValue, 7)
        profit = max(profit, 7 - minValue)
        so, `profit` = 0
    At index `1` 
        minValue = min(minValue, 1)
        profit = max(profit, 1 - 1)
        so, `profit` = 0
    At index `2` 
        minValue = min(minValue, 5)
        profit = max(profit, 5 - 1)
        so, `profit` = 4
    At index `3` 
        minValue = min(minValue, 3)
        profit = max(profit, 3 - 1)
        so, `profit` = 4
    At index `4` 
        minValue = min(minValue, 6)
        profit = max(profit, 6 - 1)
        so, `profit` = 5
    At index `5` 
        minValue = min(minValue, 4)
        profit = max(profit, 4 - 1)
        so, `profit` = 5
    So answer is `5`
